<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>I praise the synthesis and expansion of attractor theory to explain near-universals, but critique its failure to explain absolute universals. I agree that lullabies, hero stories, and shamanism are good candidates for primarily cultural evolutionary explanation, but argue that the larger, most universal categories they are sub-phenomena of -music, language, religion -require geneculture coevolutionary explanations.</p></div>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
